AGI - "Mr. Prime Minister, you and your government have not yet assumed responsibility. So many citizens ask for forgiveness, so few politicians ask for forgiveness. So many citizens and fighters assume responsibility, so few members of the government assume responsibility." It is the accusation launched by Yarden&nbsp;Bibas, former hostage and father of the two small &nbsp;Bibas, who died with his mother Shiri while in the hands of Hamas in Gaza. "83% of Israeli citizens ask for a state commission of inquiry, along with 1,500 families of the October Council, including me," added in a letter, read by the National Unit Congressman, Chili Tropper, during a special plenary session at the Knesset, during which Benjamin Netanyahu had to respond to the demands of the deputies to establish a state investigation commission on October 7. The idea for which the premier again expressed his opposition because "the conclusions would already be predetermined and written, all concentrated towards a part of the political spectrum. It is essential to thoroughly investigate everything that happened on October 7 and what brought you - he added - but this investigation must gain the trust of a large part of the people. Therefore, we ask for the establishment of an objective, balanced, independent and unpolished committee of inquiry", concluded Netanyahu.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Before the session took off, there was a real fight outside, with pushers and people on the ground, for the attempt of some family of hostages and victims of October 7 to attend the works at the &nbsp;Knesset&nbsp; from the tribune of guests. The internal guards blocked them while trying to get into the reserved area and tried to drive them away in a bad way. After the incident, however, most relatives were allowed to access the forum.&nbsp;
In protest, however, some family members turned back, giving their backs to the premier during his speech, others showed pictures of their loved ones in the hands of Hamas. The President of Parliament, Amir Ohana, has urged them to show respect without however letting them go away.
&nbsp;
